devdoc.details: This is an example implementation of the Xcert smart contract.

approve(address,uint256).details: Set or reaffirm the approved address for an NFT.

params._approved: Address to be approved for the given NFT ID.
params._tokenId: ID of the token to be approved.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of NFTs owned by `_owner`. NFTs assigned to the zero address are considered invalid, and this function throws for queries about the zero address.

params._owner: Address for whom to query the balance.

params._capabilities: Array of bytes4 representing supported interfaces which activate the corresponding capabilities.
params._name: A descriptive name for a collection of NFTs.
params._schemaId: A bytes32 of keccak256 of json schema representing 0xcert Protocol convention.
params._uriPostfix: Postfix of URI for token metadata URIs.
params._uriPrefix: Prefix of URI for token metadata URIs.

params._id: The Xcert to be created by the msg.sender.
params._to: The address that will own the created Xcert.

destroy(uint256).details: Destroys a specified Xcert. Reverts if not called from Xcert owner or operator.

params._tokenId: Id of the Xcert we want to destroy.

generateClaim(address,address,bool,addre.details: Generates hash of the set approval for.

params._approved: True if the operators is approved, false to revoke approval.
params._expiration: Timestamp of when the claim expires.
params._feeToken: The token then will be tranfered to the executor of this method.
params._feeValue: The amount of token then will be tranfered to the executor of this method.
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.
params._owner: Address to the owner who is approving.
params._seed: Arbitrary number to facilitate uniqueness of the order's hash. Usually timestamp.

getApproved(uint256).details: Get the approved address for a single NFT.

params._tokenId: ID of the NFT to query the approval of.

grantAbilities(address,uint256).details: Grants specific abilities to specified address.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are granting.

isAble(address,uint256).details: Check if an address has a specific ability. Throws if checking for 0.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are checking.
params._target: Address for which we want to check if it has a specific abilities.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Checks if `_operator` is an approved operator for `_owner`.

params._operator: The address that acts on behalf of the owner.
params._owner: The address that owns the NFTs.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).return: True if approved for all, false otherwise.

isValidSignature(address,bytes32,(bytes3.details: Verifies if claim signature is valid.

name().details: Returns a descriptive name for a collection of NFTs.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the address of the owner of the NFT. NFTs assigned to zero address are considered invalid, and queries about them do throw.

revoke(uint256).details: Revokes(destroys) a specified Xcert. Reverts if not called from contract owner or authorized address.

params._tokenId: Id of the Xcert we want to destroy.

revokeAbilities(address,uint256).details: Unassigns specific abilities from specified address.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are revoking.
params._target: Address of which we revoke abilites.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers the ownership of an NFT from one address to another address.

params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers the ownership of an NFT from one address to another address.

params._data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `_to`.
params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

schemaId().details: Returns a bytes32 of sha256 of json schema representing 0xcert Protocol convention.

setAbilities(address,uint256).details: Sets specific abilities to specified address.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are setting.
params._target: Address to which we are setting abilitites.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Enables or disables approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all of `msg.sender`'s assets. It also emits the ApprovalForAll event.

params._approved: True if the operators is approved, false to revoke approval.
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.

setApprovalForAllWithSignature(address,a.details: Enables or disables approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all of `msg.sender`'s assets. It also emits the ApprovalForAll event.

params._approved: True if the operators is approved, false to revoke approval.
params._expiration: Timestamp of when the claim expires.
params._feeToken: The token then will be tranfered to the executor of this method.
params._feeValue: The amount of token then will be tranfered to the executor of this method.
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.
params._owner: Address to the owner who is approving.
params._seed: Arbitrary number to facilitate uniqueness of the order's hash. Usually timestamp.

setPause(bool).details: Sets if Xcerts transfers are paused (can be performed) or not.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Function to check which interfaces are suported by this contract.

symbol().details: Returns an abbreviated name for NFTs.

tokenByIndex(uint256).details: Returns NFT ID by its index.

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).details: returns the n-th NFT ID from a list of owner's tokens.

params._index: Index number representing n-th token in owner's list of tokens.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Throws if `_tokenId` is not a valid NFT. URIs are defined in RFC 3986. The URI may point to a JSON file that conforms to the "ERC721 Metadata JSON Schema".

params._tokenId: Id for which we want URI.

totalSupply().details: Returns the count of all existing NFTs.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Throws unless `msg.sender` is the current owner, an authorized operator, or the approved address for this NFT. Throws if `_from` is not the current owner. Throws if `_to` is the zero address. Throws if `_tokenId` is not a valid NFT.

params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

approve(address,uint256).details: Set or reaffirm the approved address for an NFT.

params._approved: Address to be approved for the given NFT ID.
params._tokenId: ID of the token to be approved.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of NFTs owned by `_owner`. NFTs assigned to the zero address are considered invalid, and this function throws for queries about the zero address.

params._owner: Address for whom to query the balance.

params._capabilities: Array of bytes4 representing supported interfaces which activate the corresponding capabilities.
params._name: A descriptive name for a collection of NFTs.
params._schemaId: A bytes32 of keccak256 of json schema representing 0xcert Protocol convention.
params._uriPostfix: Postfix of URI for token metadata URIs.
params._uriPrefix: Prefix of URI for token metadata URIs.

params._id: The Xcert to be created by the msg.sender.
params._to: The address that will own the created Xcert.

destroy(uint256).details: Destroys a specified Xcert. Reverts if not called from Xcert owner or operator.

params._tokenId: Id of the Xcert we want to destroy.

generateClaim(address,address,bool,addre.details: Generates hash of the set approval for.

params._approved: True if the operators is approved, false to revoke approval.
params._expiration: Timestamp of when the claim expires.
params._feeToken: The token then will be tranfered to the executor of this method.
params._feeValue: The amount of token then will be tranfered to the executor of this method.
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.
params._owner: Address to the owner who is approving.
params._seed: Arbitrary number to facilitate uniqueness of the order's hash. Usually timestamp.

getApproved(uint256).details: Get the approved address for a single NFT.

params._tokenId: ID of the NFT to query the approval of.

grantAbilities(address,uint256).details: Grants specific abilities to specified address.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are granting.

isAble(address,uint256).details: Check if an address has a specific ability. Throws if checking for 0.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are checking.
params._target: Address for which we want to check if it has a specific abilities.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Checks if `_operator` is an approved operator for `_owner`.

params._operator: The address that acts on behalf of the owner.
params._owner: The address that owns the NFTs.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).return: True if approved for all, false otherwise.

isValidSignature(address,bytes32,(bytes3.details: Verifies if claim signature is valid.

name().details: Returns a descriptive name for a collection of NFTs.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the address of the owner of the NFT. NFTs assigned to zero address are considered invalid, and queries about them do throw.

revoke(uint256).details: Revokes(destroys) a specified Xcert. Reverts if not called from contract owner or authorized address.

params._tokenId: Id of the Xcert we want to destroy.

revokeAbilities(address,uint256).details: Unassigns specific abilities from specified address.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are revoking.
params._target: Address of which we revoke abilites.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers the ownership of an NFT from one address to another address.

params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

params._data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `_to`.
params._from: The current owner of the NFT.

schemaId().details: Returns a bytes32 of sha256 of json schema representing 0xcert Protocol convention.

setAbilities(address,uint256).details: Sets specific abilities to specified address.

params._abilities: Number representing bitfield of abilities we are setting.
params._target: Address to which we are setting abilitites.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Enables or disables approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all of `msg.sender`'s assets. It also emits the ApprovalForAll event.

params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.
